      "references": "[Ha74] Hayman, W. K., Research problems in function theory: new problems. (1974), 155--180.\n \n [Po59] Pommerenke, Ch., On some problems by Erd\\H{o}s, Herzog and Piranian. Michigan Math. J. (1959), 221-225.\n \n [Po61] Pommerenke, Ch., On metric properties of complex polynomials. Michigan Math. J. (1961), 97-115.",
      "remarks": "Cartan proved this is true with $2$ replaced by $2e$, which was improved to $2.59$ by Pommerenke \\cite{Po61}. Pommerenke \\cite{Po59} proved that $2$ is achievable if the set is connected (see [1046]).\n\nThe generalisation of this to higher dimensions was asked by Erd\\H{o}s as Problem 4.23 in \\cite{Ha74}."
